able%20design%2C%20Starship%20is%20essential%20to%20fulfilling%20Musk's%20ambitious%20vision%20of%20colonizing%20the%20Red%20Planet%20and%20making%20humankind%20a%20multiplanetary%20species.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3ESuper%20Heavy%20has%20splashed%20down%20in%20the%20Gulf%20of%20Mexico%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FhIY3Gkq57k%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2FhIY3Gkq57k%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%E2%80%94%20SpaceX%20(%40SpaceX)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FSpaceX%2Fstatus%2F1798701489097183286%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EJune%206%2C%202024%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENASA%20meanwhile%20has%20contracted%20a%20modified%20version%20of%20Starship%20to%20act%20as%20the%20final%20vehicle%20that%20will%20take%20astronauts%20down%20to%20the%20surface%20of%20the%20Moon%20under%20the%20Artemis%20program%20later%20this%20decade.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E-%20Trial-and-error%20approach%20-%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThree%20previous%20test%20flights%20had%20ended%20in%20Starship's%20destruction%2C%20all%20part%20of%20what%20the%20company%20says%20is%20an%20acceptable%20cost%20in%20its%20rapid%20trial-and-error%20approach%20to%20development.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20payload%20for%20these%20flight%20tests%20is%20data%2C%26quot%3B%20SpaceX%20said%20on%20X%2C%20a%20mantra%20repeated%20by%20the%20commentary%20team%20throughout%20the%20flight.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20challenge%20is%20to%20develop%20a%20%26quot%3Bfully%20and%20immediately%20reusable%20orbital%20heat%20shield%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Musk%2C%20vowing%20further%20tests%20to%20learn%20how%20to%20make%20Starship%20better%20withstand%20careening%20into%20the%20atmosphere%20at%20around%2027%2C000%20kilometers%20per%20hour%20(nearly%2017%2C000%20mph).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAbout%20seven-and-a-half%20minutes%20after%20liftoff%2C%20the%20first%20stage%20booster%2C%20called%20Super%20Heavy%2C%20succeeded%20in%20an%20upright%20splashdown%20in%20the%20Gulf%20of%20Mexico%2C%20to%20massive%20applause%20from%20engineers%20at%20mission%20control%20in%20Hawthorne%2C%20California.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20cheers%20grew%20even%20louder%20in%20the%20flight's%20final%20minutes.%20Ground%20teams%20whooped%20and%20hollered%20as%20the%20upper%20stage%20glowed%20a%20fiery%20red%2C%20the%20result%20of%20a%20plasma%20field%20generated%20by%20the%20friction%20of%20the%20vehicle%20streaking%20through%20the%20atmosphere.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpace%20fans%20around%20the%20world%20watched%20in%20awe%2C%20thanks%20to%20a%20live%20broadcast%20powered%20by%20SpaceX's%20vast%20constellation%20of%20Starlink%20internet%20satellites.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20chunk%20of%20flying%20debris%20even%20cracked%20the%20camera%20lens%2C%20but%20in%20the%20end%2C%20Starship%20stuck%20the%20landing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCongratulations%20SpaceX%20on%20Starship's%20successful%20test%20flight%20this%20morning!%26quot%3B%20NASA%20chief%20Bill%20Nelson%20wrote%20on%20X.%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20another%20step%20closer%20to%20returning%20humanity%20to%20the%20Moon%20through%20%23Artemis%20--%20then%20looking%20onward%20to%20Mars.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E-%20Twice%20as%20powerful%20as%20Apollo%20rocket%20-%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStarship%20stands%20397%20feet%20(121%20meters)%20tall%20with%20both%20stages%20combined%20--%2090%20feet%20taller%20than%20the%20Statue%20of%20Liberty.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIts%20Super%20Heavy%20booster%20produces%2016.7%20million%20pounds%20(74.3%20Meganewtons)%20of%20thrust%2C%20about%20twice%20as%20powerful%20as%20the%20Saturn%20V%20rockets%20used%20during%20the%20Apollo%20missions%2C%20and%20later%20versions%20should%20be%20more%20powerful%20still.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpaceX's%20strategy%20of%20carrying%20out%20tests%20in%20the%20real%20world%20rather%20than%20in%20labs%20has%20paid%20off%20in%20the%20past.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIts%20Falcon%209%20rockets%20have%20come%20to%20be%20workhorses%20for%20NASA%20and%20the%20commercial%20sector%2C%20its%20Dragon%20capsule%20sends%20astronauts%20and%20cargo%20to%20the%20International%20Space%20Station%2C%20and%20its%20Starlink%20internet%20satellite%20constellation%20now%20covers%20dozens%20of%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20clock%20is%20ticking%20for%20SpaceX%20to%20be%20ready%20for%20NASA's%20planned%20return%20of%20astronauts%20to%20the%20Moon%20in%202026.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20do%20this%2C%20SpaceX%20will%20need%20to%20first%20place%20a%20primary%20Starship%20in%20orbit%2C%20then%20use%20multiple%20%26quot%3BStarship%20tankers%26quot%3B%20to%20fill%20it%20up%20with%20supercooled%20fuel%20for%20the%20onward%20journey%20--%20a%20complex%20engineering%20feat%20that%20has%20never%20before%20been%20accomplished.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina%20is%20planning%20its%20own%20crewed%20lunar%20mission%20in%202030%2C%20and%20has%20recently%20had%20a%20better%20track%20record%20than%20the%20United%20States%20of%20adhering%20to%20its%20timelines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1717725780000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-06%2Fvrhonfeo_spacex_625x300_07_June_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fspacexs-megarocket-starship-nails-historic-ocean-splashdown-5835757%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22SpaceX's%20massive%20Starship%20rocket%20achieved%20its%20first%20ever%20splashdown%20during%20a%20test%20flight%20Thursday%2C%20in%20a%20major%20milestone%20for%20the%20prototype%20system%20that%20may%20one%20day%20send%20humans%20to%20Mars.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworl